Please note that while emojis are universally recognized, their appearance may vary depending on the device and platform where your page is viewed.

Ah, I see you're interested in a more animated effect, similar to Asana's celebrations for task completions. 

For a full-page overlay, we can add a semi-transparent overlay to the page, and for the unicorn flying across the screen, we can animate an image. Please note that animations typically require more complex CSS and JavaScript.

Here's a simple example that features a full-page overlay and a unicorn image that moves from left to right when the slider reaches its maximum value.

This is just a basic demonstration of how such an effect could be achieved and would need to be enhanced to suit your specific needs:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
        .container {
            width: 80%;
            margin: auto;
            position: relative;
            height: 10px;
            background-color: #d3d3d3;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

        .slider {
            position: absolute;
            height: 20px;
            width: 20px;
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            border-radius: 50%;
            left: 50%;
            top: 50%;
            transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
        }

        #display {
            margin-top: 20px;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 2em;
        }

        #overlay {
            position: fixed;
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            display: none;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
        }

        #celebration {
            font-size: 5em;
        }

        @keyframes slide {
            from {
                transform: translateX(-100%);
            }

            to {
                transform: translateX(100%);
            }
        }

        #unicorn {
            display: none;
            animation: slide 2s linear;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container" id="container">
        <div class="slider" id="slider"></div>
    </div>

    <div id="display">
        0.0000000000
    </div>

    <div id="overlay">
        <img id="unicorn" src="https://your-url-to-unicorn-image.com/unicorn.png" alt="Unicorn">
        <div id="celebration">ðŸŽ‰</div>
    </div>

    <script>
        const slider = document.getElementById('slider');
        const container = document.getElementById('container');
        const display = document.getElementById('display');
        const overlay = document.getElementById('overlay');
        const celebration = document.getElementById('celebration');
        const unicorn = document.getElementById('unicorn');
        let sliderPos = 0;
        let mouseDown = false;
        let startX, endX;

        const updatePosition = () => {
            const newPos = Math.min(Math.max(sliderPos, 0), container.offsetWidth - slider.offsetWidth);
            slider.style.left = `${newPos}px`;
            const val = ((newPos - container.offsetWidth / 2) / container.offsetWidth * 10).toFixed(10);
            display.textContent = val;

            // Celebration when reaching highest value
            if (newPos >= container.offsetWidth - slider.offsetWidth - 1) {
                overlay.style.display = 'flex';
                unicorn.style.display = 'block';
                setTimeout(() => {
                    overlay.style.display = 'none';
                    unicorn.style.display = 'none';
                }, 2000);
            }
        }

        slider.addEventListener('mousedown', (event) => {
            mouseDown = true;
            startX = event.clientX;
        });

        document.addEventListener('mouseup', () => {
            mouseDown = false;
        });

        document.addEventListener('mousemove', (event) => {
            if (mouseDown) {
                endX = event.clientX;
                let diff = (endX - startX);
                const centerFraction = 2 * Math.abs(sliderPos / container.offsetWidth - 0.5);
                diff /= 10 * (centerFraction * centerFraction) + 1;
                sliderPos += diff;
                updatePosition();
                startX = endX;
            }
        });

        // Initial position set
        sliderPos = container.offsetWidth / 2;
        updatePosition();
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

In this code, you would need to replace `https://your-url-to-unicorn-image.com/unicorn.png` with the actual URL of your unicorn image. The celebration is triggered when the slider position is within 1 pixel of the maximum. A full-page overlay is shown, and a unicorn image is animated to move across the screen from left to right. The celebration lasts for 2 seconds and then disappears.

Note: Be sure that you have the rights to use the unicorn image and that it's hosted somewhere accessible from your website. The look and feel of the overlay and celebration can be adjusted by changing the CSS styles. The 2-second duration of the celebration can be adjusted by changing the argument to the `setTimeout` function.

